{"title":"Mayhem","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Mayhem","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                           |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | It causes witnesses of the wearer's kills to go into a frenzy, attacking everything nearby with great strength and speed. |\n\n**Mayhem** is an [ego](/Ego \"Ego\") found only on [orbs](/Orb \"Orb\"). Characters wielding an orb of mayhem have a 50% chance of inflicting [frenzy](/Frenzy \"Frenzy\") on another monster whenever they kill a foe. Frenzied monsters are [neutral](/Neutral \"Neutral\"), attack the closest thing (friend or foe), and gain immense power and speed ([might](/Might \"Might\") and [haste](/Haste \"Haste\")).\n\n## Strategy\n\n- Mayhem is most useful in areas you know will be filled with monsters; areas like [Vaults](/Vaults \"Vaults\"):5 or a [Ziggurat](/Ziggurat \"Ziggurat\").\n- Whilst very powerful when fighting a group, be aware that it can backfire. For example, it can frenzy your own [summons](/Summon \"Summon\"), or enrage the only enemy left alive.\n  - There are a few ways to deal with dangerous frenzied monsters that target you. [Spriggans](/Spriggan \"Spriggan\") can easily outrun even hasted monsters, other characters can [teleport](/Teleport \"Teleport\") away, and you can dispel frenzy with [Yara's Violent Unravelling](/Yara%27s_Violent_Unravelling \"Yara's Violent Unravelling\") or a [wand of quicksilver](/Wand_of_quicksilver \"Wand of quicksilver\").\n\n## History\n\nThe mayhem ego, along with orbs themselves, was introduced in [0.28](/0.28 \"0.28\").\n\n| [Orbs](/Orb \"Orb\")                                                                                                    |\n| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| [Energy](/Energy \"Energy\") • [Guile](/Guile \"Guile\") • [Light](/Light \"Light\") • [Mayhem]() • [Wrath](/Wrath \"Wrath\") |\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Mayhem - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Mayhem\",\"wgTitle\":\"Mayhem\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":70107,\"wgRevisionId\":70107,\"wgArticleId\":10636,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"0.30 articles\",\"Orbs\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Mayhem\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":10636,\"wgRequestId\":\"03320cbbd9c0ea5dd7f5af94\",\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[]});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"loading\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"ext.smw.style\":\"ready\",\"ext.smw.tooltip.styles\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\