teargumentsize\":{\"value\":124,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":4,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%   94.013      1 -total\",\" 67.85%   63.785      1 Template:Version030\",\" 59.93%   56.340      1 Template:Version\",\" 29.44%   27.682      1 Template:Orb\",\"  1.95%    1.833      1 Template:Flavour\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240916223312\",\"ttl\":86400,\"transientcontent\":false}}});});</script><script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":374});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{version030}}\n{{flavour|It causes witnesses of the wearer's kills to go into a frenzy, attacking everything nearby with great strength and speed.}}\n\n'''Mayhem''' is an [[ego]] found only on [[orb]]s. Characters wielding an orb of mayhem have a 50% chance of inflicting [[frenzy]] on another monster whenever they kill a foe. Frenzied monsters are [[neutral]], attack the closest thing (friend or foe), and gain immense power and speed ([[might]] and [[haste]]).\n\n==Strategy==\n*Mayhem is most useful in areas you know will be filled with monsters; areas like [[Vaults]]:5 or a [[Ziggurat]].\n*Whilst very powerful when fighting a group, be aware that it can backfire. For example, it can frenzy your own [[summon]]s, or enrage the only enemy left alive.\n**There are a few ways to deal with dangerous frenzied monsters that target you. [[Spriggan]]s can easily outrun even hasted monsters, other characters can [[teleport]] away, and you can dispel frenzy with [[Yara's Violent Unravelling]] or a [[wand of quicksilver]].\n\n==History==\nThe mayhem ego, along with orbs themselves, was introduced in [[0.28]].\n\n{{orb}}"}